title: Add a default contact reason. (#91)
message:
Add a default contact reason. (#91)

* Add a default contact reason.

Addresses: https://github.com/5calls/android/issues/43

Test Plan:
- Run the app on an Android emulator.
- Navigate to a "rep call" screen. See reason for calling displayed as usual.
- Temporarily set `contact.reason` to `""` before setting up the UI and re-run the app. (Since I'm not sure if there are any current issues that don't have reasons specfied.)
- Navigate to a "rep call" screen. See default reason: "This organization is driving legislation related to the issue."

* Replace `isEmpty` with `TextUtils#isEmpty`.

title: Allow users to send an email from the about page. (#90)
message:
Allow users to send an email from the about page. (#90)

* Allow users to send an email from the about page.

Begins to address: https://github.com/5calls/android/issues/60

Test Plan:
- Run the app on an Android emulator.
- Navigate to the "about page."
- Scroll down and click "contact us" button.
- See email client selector (if 0 or > 1 email clients are installed) and select one.
- Ensure email is automatically populated with the email address "make5calls@gmail.com" and the subject line "Feedback from 5 Calls Android App".

* Add contact us prompt.

title: Add support for Jellybean (API 16+)
message:
Add support for Jellybean (API 16+)

This breaks internationalization for RTL layouts because Jellybean
does not support *_start and *_end, but needs *_left and *_right.
However we don't seem to need to support RTL languages in the near
future so this can be addressed later.

Part of issue #10.
